docs.lead_paragraph: After an anti-abortion group released surreptitiously recorded videos of Planned Parenthood personnel in discussions about providing fetal tissue for research, Texas Attorney General Ken Paxton, a pro-life Republican, pledged to "aggressively" investigate whether the women's health organization had violated the law.
